Initial files present before the agent starts:

    1. /home/user/release/env_schema.json  
       Content (minified to avoid whitespace ambiguity):
       {
         "$schema":"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
         "type":"object",
         "required":["version","services"],
         "properties":{
           "version":{"type":"string","pattern":"^[0-9]+\\.[0-9]+\\.[0-9]+$"},
           "services":{
             "type":"array",
             "minItems":1,
             "items":{
               "type":"object",
               "required":["name","image","ports"],
               "properties":{
                 "name":{"type":"string"},
                 "image":{"type":"string"},
                 "ports":{
                   "type":"array",
                   "minItems":1,
                   "items":{"type":"integer","minimum":1,"maximum":65535}
                 }
               },
               "additionalProperties":false
             }
           }
         },
         "additionalProperties":false
       }

    2. /home/user/release/env_descriptor.json  
       Content (minified):
       {"version":"1.4.0","services":[{"name":"auth-service","image":"registry.example.com/auth:1.4.0","ports":[8080]},{"name":"payments-service","image":"registry.example.com/payments:2.1.3","ports":[9000,9001]}]}

    Expected artefacts after successful completion:

    A. /home/user/release/validation.log  
       Content (with single trailing newline):
       STATUS: VALID\n

    B. /home/user/release/release_summary.csv  
       Content (with single trailing newline):
       auth-service,registry.example.com/auth:1.4.0\n
       payments-service,registry.example.com/payments:2.1.3\n

    File permissions for both A and B: 0644 (rw-r--r-- or more permissive).

    The agent’s final console output (stdout) must show, in this order:

    1. The content of validation.log exactly as above (including the newline which appears as a line break).  
    2. Immediately followed by the two lines from release_summary.csv in the same order, each on its own line.

    Anything printed before or after those three lines will be ignored by the grader, but the three lines must appear consecutively and match exactly.
